They‚Äôre here!!! We are so excited to begin our transition to using biodegradable tattoo supplies, starting with biodegradable gloves from the excellent Toronto- based @goodjudy.ca. In the coming months we look forward to replacing our razors and plastic hygienic products with biodegradable razors and barrier film.
Other goals to reduce the waste we produce at Catalpa:
-donate paper scraps to a local paper making company
-turn our full page paper waste into hand-made books
Other actions we are taking to support climate justice:
-starting this week there will be ‚ÄúPerverts Against Pipelines‚Äù t-shirts for sale in our little boutique. All profits from their sales will go to the Unist‚Äôot‚Äôen Legal Defence fund which needs our support more than ever.

Exciting news from @catalpastudio : starting next week we‚Äôre moving to a larger space! We are thrilled to expand our little community into a studio that we hope will make your experience with us even better. We will be closed for renovations starting next week until the New Year when we can‚Äôt wait to host you in our new space. All appointments still stand with @lucitattoos and @karen.nine.fingers unless your hear otherwise from them. The new studio is in the same building and right next door to our current one. We are so grateful to our incredible community and clientele for your ongoing support- this wouldn‚Äôt be possible without you! We are also grateful to the little  studio we have called our home for the last year and a half- it has brought wonderful things to both of us and to those that walk though its door. Happy end of  decade and we‚Äôll be posting in-progress shots of the new space next week! Here‚Äôs to new beginnings for 2020!!! Love,  Luci and Karen üñ§

Hey all! @karen.nine.fingers is taking part in a fundraiser in a couple of weeks for the Unist‚Äôot‚Äôen legal fund. We are very excited to help support this important initiative and they are donating a $150 flash tattoo to be raffled off at the  screening at NDQ Montreal (more details below)where you can buy tickets the evening of the event. 100% of proceeds will go to the legal fund! 
If you are unable to attend the event but would like a chance to win/ donate to the fund you can follow these steps: 
1. Repost this post on your feed or story.

2. Buy raffle tickets: $5 for 1 and $20 for 5 tix! You can purchase them by sending your desired amount to queersforqlimatejustice@gmail.com- be sure to send a separate email with your name and IG handle so we know where to find you if you win :) 3. We will put your name on a raffle ticket and draw the lucky winner at the event on December 15th! 
4. Ticket sales end December 14th so get your tickets now and support this important act of solidarity with Indigenous land defenders! 
Here‚Äôs the info for the event: (more info at https://facebook.com/events/s/queers4qlimatejustice-screenin/729805217525427) ***Queers for Qlimate Justice present: Screening of INVASION and Woman at War
A fundraiser for the Unist‚Äôot‚Äôen Legal Fund

Sunday December 15 @ NDQ (32 Beaubien Est)
5pm: NDQ opens and t-shirt sales begin
6pm: Screening of INVASION + Woman at War 
Stick around after to do some scheming and karaoke! 
All funds raised will go to the Unist‚Äôot‚Äôen legal fund.

Join some queers for climate justice for a cozy and catalyzing winter screening at NDQ. We‚Äôll watch two great films about resisting big energy projects, and you‚Äôll be able to pick up the Perverts Against Pipelines t-shirts and hoodies you were wanting to bring home to your family and friends for the holigays! ***
